This article deals with billboards located at the Minhocao, in the city of Sao Paulo, before the law “Clean City”, and its goal is to exam the kinds of signs present in the urban scene in Sao Paulo, which are represented by the Minhocao. The methodological strategy was based on the photographs of billboards and semiotic analyses of those, supported by Charles Sanders’s semiotic, Ferrara’s ideas about the city as a sign system, the word studies developed by Noth and Santaella as well as the ideas presented by Bataille about the erotic.